<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="468" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Endrodi, 1978" authorityName="Endrodi" authorityYear="1978" box="[322,694,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malyi">
<emphasis box="[322,527,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Eophileurus malyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Endrodi, S." box="[534,694,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" pagination="183 - 185" refId="ref16975" refString="Endrodi, S. (1978) Zwei neue Eophileurus Arten aus Thailand. Annales historico-naturales Musei nationalis hungarici, 70, 183 - 185." type="journal article" year="1978">Endrődi, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1029,1129,151,177]" name="Thailand" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Thailand</collectingCountry>
with no additional material known to literature since its discovery. The 
<typeStatus box="[660,708,187,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">type</typeStatus>
series (
<figureCitation box="[800,938,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–78" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1375,186,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-18@15.[202,1386,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 71–78. Type specimens of Eophileurus malyi Endrődi, 1978 (images ©HNHM/Ottó Merkl). 71–75, holotype, male, 71, habitus, dorsal; 72, habitus, lateral; 73, parameres, apical; 74, parameres, lateral; 75, labels; 76–77, paratype, female, 76, habitus, dorsal; 77, habitus, lateral; 78, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853966" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853966/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Figs. 71–78</figureCitation>
) clearly suggest its close relationship to 
<taxonomicName authority="Prell, 1913" authorityName="Prell" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eophileurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confinis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">E. confinis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Prell, H." box="[248,372,223,249]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" pagination="103 - 124" refId="ref17521" refString="Prell, H. (1913) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Dynastinen. viii. Ueber das Genus Eophilurus Arrow. Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 22, 103 - 124." type="journal article" year="1913">Prell, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but the parameres are structurally different in having an extra pair of backward process at the center of the parameres in frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[600,685,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–78" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1375,186,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-18@15.[202,1386,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 71–78. Type specimens of Eophileurus malyi Endrődi, 1978 (images ©HNHM/Ottó Merkl). 71–75, holotype, male, 71, habitus, dorsal; 72, habitus, lateral; 73, parameres, apical; 74, parameres, lateral; 75, labels; 76–77, paratype, female, 76, habitus, dorsal; 77, habitus, lateral; 78, labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6853966" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6853966/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
